MELROSE PUBLIC LIBRARY - PADDLE BOSTON SPOT POND PASS: &nbsp;&nbsp;
This pass is valid for online reservations and walk-up rentals at Spot Pond , in Stoneham, MA ( valid only for date printed on the pass ) .&nbsp;
This pass&nbsp; allows 1 boat rental &nbsp; free of charge at Spot Pond (there are options for boats that will seat more than 1 person).&nbsp; If you are reserving more than 1 boat on your visit, you may need to make a second reservation for the boat(s) not covered by the discount pass.&nbsp; The pass does not include use of sailboats or provide guaranteed parking.&nbsp; You will need to fill out a Float Plan Agreement ONE time per season.&nbsp;
Patrons may reserve the pass up to 2 times per month.
Reserve your Melrose Public Library pass for desired date.&nbsp; You will receive a confirmation email with an&nbsp; "Access Pass" link (if you do not have an email account, a printed confirmation may be picked up at the Main Desk of the library).

MELROSE PUBLIC LIBRARY – PEABODY ESSEX MUSEUM PASS&nbsp;&nbsp;
This pass admits 2 people with a $12 co-pay per person (Thursday through Monday- children 16 and under are free, but still require a reservation).&nbsp;&nbsp; The library pass may only be used for the date printed on the pass.&nbsp; The library pass does not guarantee admission on a chosen date.&nbsp; Please visit the PEM website to review museum visitor requirements and any updates to operating hours.&nbsp; The library pass reservation calendar may not reflect changes to museum open dates and hours of operation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;
Reserve your Melrose Public Library pass for desired date.&nbsp; You will receive a confirmation email with an&nbsp; "Access Pass" link (if you do not have an email account, a printed confirmation may be picked up at the Main Desk of the library).
THE LIBRARY PASS DOES NOT GUARANTEE ADMISSION
Funded by the City of Melrose
